half of what he wants in order to protect crime victims but that 
he wanted an ample opportunity for full discussion before 
attempting further changes 
the bill in addition to the repeal would prohibit using crime 
victim information obtained from law enforcement agencies to solicit 
business from the victim or a family member of the victim 
the prohibition would apply to victims who were injured in a 
crime or whose home was illegally entered 
the bill would give the attorney general power to sue under the 
deceptive trade practices act to stop such use of the information 
violation of the law would be punishable by civil penalties up to 
10000 plus court costs and attorneys fees 
the repeal would be immediate and the solicitation section would 
take effect jan 1 
