<TEXT>
harvey w georges 71 who covered eight 
presidents during a career that spanned 41 years as an associated 
press photographer died thursday 
georges who had been under treatment for cancer died after a 
heart attack at a health care residence in nearby reston 
he joined the ap in washington in august 1941 bent on becoming a 
photographer he reached that goal in 1945 after serving as a 
dictationist copy boy wirephoto operator and darkroom technician 
he photographed presidents from harry s truman to ronald reagan 
covered congress space shots demonstrations political campaigns 
and conventions and along the way became known for his 
doublejointed humor as well as his photos he could stand with one 
foot on the floor and one near the ceiling and sometimes did 
he made exclusive photographs of the pennsylvania avenue scene 
after the attempted assassination of truman in 1950 a shooting in 
which one policeman was killed and another wounded 
one memorable georges photo was of actress lauren becall sitting 
atop trumans piano 
georges retired from the ap in 1982 
he was born on april 19 1918 in evansville ind and will be 
buried there 
doris georges his wife of 44 years died in january 1986 
he leaves two daughters mrs diannah pennington and mrs malinda 
gilbert of mclean and two grandchildren 
