report and to the newcomers flies and barnyard odors arent part 
of their idyllic country dream 
some flies can travel great distances from manure piles or other 
barnyard breeding places to find targets the stable fly can migrate 
up to 135 miles 
bram is the national program leader for insects affecting humans 
at the agencys research facility in beltsville md 
we have to learn how to increase nonchemical fly control and 
how to make the save chemicals we have work better he said it 
goes beyond relying on screen doors sprays and swatters 
possible tactics include nonchemical baits in traps to lure 
flies natural predators such as wasps that prey on flies while in 
their pupa stage of development and natural organisms such as fungi 
and bacteria that attack flies in cattle feedlots 
the usda attack is directed at four main kinds of flies 
stable flies which have biting mouth parts and feed on blood 
house flies which secrete digestive enzymes onto their food 
then suck up both enzymes and food 
horn flies which bother only livestock on pastures and 
rangeland 
