specialty medical centers all the centers will be open and staffed 
by physicians and other staff nudelman said 
group health began hiring nonunion nurses and preparing to lay 
off nonnursing staff in preparation for whats expected to be a 
long strike nudelman said the layoffs were intended to save money 
diane sosne president of local 1199 of the national union and 
health care employees said the talks broke off because group health 
refused to compromise on key issues particularly staffing decisions 
