in gila national forest that burned more than 10000 acres before 
being contained on monday the blaze began june 30 and burned 50 
miles northeast of silver city 
the fire should be controlled in two to four days ms garcia 
said 
fires in arizona california colorado nebraska and utah were 
largely contained thursday firefighters mostly mopped up and 
monitored hot spots 
ash kicked up by the new mexico blaze had settled in diamond 
creek choking off oxygen and possibly boosting the waters 
alkalinity 
the netted fish were to be transported in 250gallon aerated 
tanks aboard two trucks to a hatchery run by the us bureau of 
indian affairs on the mescalero apache reservation in southcentral 
new mexico said ms garcia 
she said the fish are fairly hardy 
gila trout once were widespread in mountain streams in the gila 
river basin but timber cutting overgrazing irrigation and the 
introduction of rainbow trout have diminished their numbers 
the fish has been on the federal endangered species list since 
1967 
the rescue was undertaken by the state department of game and 
fish the us fish and wildlife service and the forest service 
in utah fire bosses took a waitandsee attitude thursday on the 
states only active wildfire a 100acre blaze in an inaccessible 
area of desolation canyon 140 miles southeast of salt lake city 
the fire was within a mile of an uintah and ouray indian reservation 
and threatened important deer and elk winter ranges said bureau of 
land management district manager gene nodine 
if the fire does make a major run we would have to wait until 
it reached a more accessible less hazardous area to actively 
suppress it he said 
humidity rose significantly in eastern utah helping firefighters 
subdue a 4500acre fire 28 miles from grand junction colo thirty 
miles to the northwest firefighters demobilized after battling a 
