<TEXT>
the senate on thursday approved an overhaul of 
the immigration system that would limit new arrivals to 630000 in 
each of the next three years and expand the number coming from 
western europe 
this bill not only carries forward and increases the present 
emphasis on family reunification it also opens opportunities for 
new immigrants with new skills said sen edward m kennedy 
dmass one of the bills sponsors 
the bill approved 8117 after two days of debate now goes to 
the house it was originally designed to cap immigration at 600000 
in each of the next three years but was expanded by 30000 visas 
before final passage 
the ceiling represents 136000 more visas than were issued in 
1988 but but critics say the bill still could reduce visas for all 
but the closest relatives of american citizens and permanent 
residents of the united states 
the senate approved a similar bill in 1988 but it died in the 
house 
the measure now goes to the house with kennedy and the measures 
cosponsor sen alan k simpson rwyo saying they are optimistic 
about the prospects this year 
lawmakers voted 7821 to expand the cap by 30000 visas a year 
following an emotional appeal from sen arlen specter rpa who 
recalled how his father fled the boot of the czar in 1911 and 
arrived in america with no rubles in his pocket he had to come 
steerage 
there is nothing magic to me about the number 600000 
specter said 
