<TEXT>
the members of the sandinista 
directorate have not changed since the overthrow of dictator 
anastasio somoza a decade ago 
their unity has surprised foreign diplomats who had expected a 
split among the nine commanders of the revolution no such problem 
has arisen although some former guerrilla leaders and sympathizers 
have gone over to the antisandinista resistance 
members of the sandinista national liberation front directorate 
control the executive legislature police army and other key 
posts some wellknown officials such as vice president sergio 
ramirez and foreign minister miguel descoto are not among the nine 
these are the directorates members 
daniel ortega 43 president and likely sandinista presidential 
candidate in general elections scheduled for feb 25 his leadership 
style hard work and a decisionmaking process that is open to 
many opinions has done much to hold the directorate together 
humberto ortega 47 defense minister opponents refer to the 
government of the ortega brothers reflecting the widespread 
attitude that together as in cuba with fidel and raul castro in 
the same posts they represent the real power in nicaragua 
bayardo arce 39 as vicecoordinator of the sandinista 
executive commission arce is ortegas deputy for ideology he is 
described as an ideological hardliner and the main link between the 
sandinistas and salvadoran guerrillas 
tomas borge 58 the directorates senior member who helped 
found the sandinistas in july 1961 and is known as a hardliner as 
interior minister he is in charge of police and state security 
luis carrion 37 minister of economy industry and commerce 
carrion was born into one of nicaraguas wealthiest families 
carlos nunez 38 president of the national assembly the 
unicameral legislature 
henry ruiz hernandez 49 minister of external cooperation since 
1985 and planning minister before that 
victor tirado 49 head of the department of mass organizations 
tirado born in mexico joined the sandinistas in 1963 and became a 
nicaraguan citizen in september 1979 
jaime wheelock 42 agriculture minister and son of a wealthy 
landowning family 
