<TEXT>
an antinuclear group that has led a general 
electric co boycott for three years released figures thursday aimed 
at showing the campaign has cost the corporate giant 506 million 
in lost business ge rejected the claims 
the group infact based the calculation on the number of people 
whom it said have joined the boycott in an attempt to drive ge and 
other defense contractors out of the nuclear weapons industry 
ge wants you to think it brings good things to life said 
nancy cole executive director of the group it also brings death 
and destruction we think thats got to be stopped 
infact stands for infant formula action coalition the 
bostonbased group organized a boycott of the nestle co a decade 
ago to stop that company from selling what infact said was unsafe 
powdered babys milk the group switched to the ge boycott in july 
1986 and has claimed widespread success 
by infacts calculations at least 253 million people worldwide 
have stopped buying ge products because of the boycott resulting in 
lost revenue to the company of 2532 million in heavily populated 
areas of the united states and an equal amount elsewhere 
ge spokesman george jamison rejected infacts assertions 
anybody can claim anything jamison said the facts of the 
matter are since 1985 ge revenues are up 56 percent from 32 
billion to 50 billion earnings are up 49 percent also during that 
time market share has increased in all ge consumer businesses 
these are facts which are reported in our annual report they speak 
for themselves 
ge based in fairfield conn makes products ranging from 
dishwashers to jet engines to hightech medical equipment it is one 
of the nations leading defense contractors and the fifthlargest 
us industrial concern 
the company also owns the nbc television network and a 
controlling interest in kidder peabody group inc a large wall 
street investment firm 
infact has targeted ge because of what it calls the companys 
extensive involvement in the production and promotion of nuclear 
weaons and the trail of radioactive and toxic waste the companys 
nuclear weapons work leaves behind 
jamison said infacts goal is unilateral disarmament we want 
peace every bit as much as infact does but along with a majority of 
the american people ge believes it can be assured only by a strong 
national defense 
