<TEXT>
the federal deposit insurance corp was named 
managing agent thursday for nine savings and loans institutions in 
the new joint federal regulatory oversight program 
the federal savings and loan insurance corp named the fdic 
managing agent for four institutions in texas two in nebraska two 
in oklahoma and one in indiana federal regulators transferred all 
deposits offices and substantially all of their assets and certain 
liabilities to newly created federal mutual institutions 
depositors are not affected in any way by the action and can 
continue to transact business as usual said m danny wall chairman 
of the federal home loan bank 
placed in receivership thursday and issued new federal charters 
by the federal home loan bank board were pioneer federal savings 
and loan association plymouth ind cornerstone savngs 
association houston first federal savings and loan association 
waco texas and cross roads savings and loan association checotah 
okla 
the four insolvent institutions make a total of 237 savings and 
loans in 33 states under fdic management 
the federal home loan bank board said thursdays action was taken 
to conserve the associations assets the four new institutions did 
not assume any obligations to stockholders or holder of subordinated 
debt of the insolvent thrifts 
the remaining five institutions have been under joint 
conservatorship of the fslic and the fdic for months continental 
federal savings and loan association oklahoma city began march 16 
san antonio savings association san antonio texas joined march 2 
centennial savings bank greenville texas joined april 6 and both 
occidentalnebraska federal savings bank omaha and platte valley 
federal savings and loan association gering neb joined feb 17 
in nebraska the newly chartered mutual associations are 
occidental nebraska savings bank fsb and platte valley savings 
in texas the new associations are san antonio savings 
association fa centennial federal savings and loan association 
fa and first savings and loan association fa centennial federal 
assumed no obligations to the stockholders of the former insolvent 
thrift 
in oklahoma the new associations are continental federal savings 
and loan association fa and cross roads savings and loan 
association fa 
the new association in indiana is pioneer savings fa 
officials said the institutions will operate as usual and will 
continue to maintain the same business hours 
the joint regulatory oversight teams lead by the fdic include 
staff from the federal home loan bank board the federal savings and 
loan insurance corp the office of the comptroller of the currency 
and the federal reserve board 
as managing agent the fdic works to conserve assets and preserve 
banking services until congress approves funds for a permanent 
solution to sampl problems 
